Subject:
A Confab Session with S "Sundi" Sundaresh

Body:
Dear everyone,

One of our esteemed alumnus, Mr. S "Sundi"Sundaresh is visiting campus on
the 15th of November (Tuesday) and is willing to have a Confab session with
students interested in entrepreneurship and management.

Date: 15th November 2016

Time: 5 pm

Venue: ICSR Conference Room (Second floor)

S "Sundi"Sundaresh holds a B.Tech. degree in electrical engineering from
the Indian Institute of Technology Madras, an MS degree in electrical
engineering from Cornell University, and an MBA from The Wharton School at
the University of Pennsylvania.

He has held various positions at Hyundai Electronics, HewlettPackard,
and National Semiconductor and spent a number of years at Adaptec over two
separate periods. Initially Sundaresh served in a number of positions at
Adaptec and eventually served as the President and CEO of the company.

Sundaresh was president and CEO of Jetstream Communications in July 1998
which pioneered voice over Internet Protocol technology. Later he became
the president and CEO of Candera Inc. (formerly Confluence Networks) in
September 2002, which marketed a network storage controller. Sundaresh was
also named to the board of directors of SandForce in June 2010. He also
joined GridGain Systems as its board of directors in October 2013. Soon
after, he was also appointed as president and chief executive officer
of Xangati in November 2013.

(Above profile obtained from Wikipedia)

